snippet.textDisplay: I get the desire to be tested, but it changes little. You should be self-isolating regardless. Your friend shouldn't have traveled and gone out. Tests are being rationed so we can know how to treat those with severe symptoms and who to isolate inside hospitals and for testing hospital staff. Saying "Well if you'r not going to test me I'm going to act like I'm fine" is selfish and childish and I'll just blame it on you for refusing to test me. That's called acting entitled. I don't know the whole story, but that's how it comes off. ESPECIALLY if you're having symptoms that are congruous with the virus. We need to get over the "I'm going stir crazy and need to get out" selfishness or the "this is ruining plans" BS. yes, we need more testing, but we also need to take personal responsibility until (and even after) that becomes more available.
